oc:kn_242d37cc a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or editing marketing copy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Match transition tone to audience: B2B content can be slightly more formal; B2C benefits from conversational transitions. Vary transitions across the piece — repeating the same phrase is noticeable. Don't over-signpost; trust the reader." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tone-matched, varied transitions maintain reader trust and engagement while supporting scannability" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_674b064f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring long-form marketing content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Select transitions by rhetorical purpose: preview structure → introduce topics → refer back → move between sections → indicate relationships (addition/contrast/similarity/cause-effect) → give examples → emphasize points → provide evidence → summarize → conclude. Place transitions at paragraph starts for scannability." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Purposeful signposting improves readability, user engagement, and helps search engines understand content structure" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_69270ac4 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting any transitional phrase" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid these AI-tell transition phrases: 'That being said', 'It's worth noting that', 'At its core', 'In today's digital landscape', 'When it comes to the realm of', 'This begs the question', 'Let's delve into'. Also avoid overusing 'moreover' and 'furthermore' — they sound AI-generated. Never start a concluding paragraph with 'In conclusion'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These phrases are heavily overused in AI-generated content and signal non-human authorship to both readers and detection tools" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_6ddcba73 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reviewing copy for naturalness" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every sentence does not need a transition. Read aloud — if it sounds forced, simplify. Refer to seo-audit skill's ai-writing-detection.md for the complete AI tells list." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-signposting breaks flow and signals inauthentic writing; the complete AI tells reference catches patterns this skill may not cover" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_cb30df80 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When making qualified or non-absolute claims in copy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use hedging language (may, might, tends to, generally, often, evidence suggests) for claims that aren't absolute. Front-load key info — put the important word or phrase early in the transition." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hedging maintains credibility without weakening the argument; front-loading helps skimmers and improves readability" ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

